`modules/after.js` (lines 1-8) is the exact Underscore.js `after` utility function. The code:
```js
export default function after(times, func) {
  return function() {
    if (--times < 1) {
      return func.apply(this, arguments);
    }
  };
}
```
On every invocation, `times` is pre-decremented. Once `times` reaches 0 (the Nth call), `func` is called. On the (N+1)th and all subsequent calls, `times` goes to -1, -2, etc., and `--times < 1` remains `true`, so `func` fires **unboundedly**.

